<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4612034>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 15. Tropical lowland evergreen rain forest on hillsides above rocky stream bed, Kuala Navusu, 38 m. During the night, Echiothrix centrosa (AMNH 225678; see table 12) and Rattus hoffmanni were caught upstream where a decaying tree trunk spanned the rocky creek bed; the squirrels Prosciurillus alstoni and Rubrisciurus rubriventer were taken during the day on the same spot. The rats Maxomys hellwaldii and Paruromys dominator were frequently trapped on this hillside forest as well as six other species of murines (see table 12). Photographed in 1975." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4612034/files/figure.png" .

