<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4612019>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 11. Ventral views of the unilocular-hemiglandular stomach (in midfrontal section) of Rattus hoffmanni (AMNH 226041) and the bilocular-discoglandular stomach of Maxomys hellwaldii (AMNH 224939) contrasted with the unilocular-pouched stomach of Echiothrix centrosa (AMNH 225043). Abbreviations: a, antrum; bf, bordering fold; c, corpus; ce, cornified squamous epithelium; d, anterior end of duodenum; e, posterior end of esophagus; fv, fornix ventricularis; ge, glandular epithelium; gp, glandular pouch; ia, incisura angularis; mc, muscular walls of the corpus; p, pylorus; ps, pyloric sphincter. Scale lines 5 10 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4612019/files/figure.png" .

